a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes z P Q :: "real \<Rightarrow> real"
assumes h0 : "\<forall> z. P z = 9 * z powr 3 - 27 * z powr 2 + 27 * z"
and h1 : "\<forall> z. Q z = 9 * z * (z powr 2 - 3 * z + 3)"
shows  "\<forall> z. P z = Q z"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Factor $9z^3 - 27z^2 + 27z$. The final Answer is 9z(z^2 - 3z + 3)
 ### Proof
 Both 9 and $z$ are factors of each term, so we can factor out $9z$: \[9z^3 -27z^2 + 27z = (9z)\cdot(z^2) - (9z)\cdot (3z) + (9z)\cdot 3 = \boxed{9z(z^2 - 3z + 3)}.\]
 *)

theorem
fixes z P Q :: "real \<Rightarrow> real"
assumes h0 : "\<forall> z. P z = 9 * z powr 3 - 27 * z powr 2 + 27 * z"
and h1 : "\<forall> z. Q z = 9 * z * (z powr 2 - 3 * z + 3)"
shows  "\<forall> z. P z = Q z"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
a_0.informal problem: Show that the two functions $P(z) = 9z^3 - 27z^2 + 27z$ and $Q(z) = 9z(z^2 - 3z + 3)$ are equal for all values of $z$.
